---
// AegisPay module page (English) — spec v1.2 §3.3. KYB-critical page:
// this URL is submitted directly in MoonPay/Transak KYB applications; wording must
// stay aligned with the KYB questionnaire business-model description.
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="AegisPay — A conversation-aware risk-gating layer for payments"
  description="AegisPay is AegisTalk's built-in payment risk-gating module. Non-custodial architecture — AegisRD never holds customer funds. Fiat on/off-ramp handled by licensed ramp partners. Core on-chain testing complete; launches with AegisTalk."
  lang="en"
  altPath="/aegistalk/pay"
  active="pay"
>
  <section class="hero" style="min-height:65vh">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="hero-badge"><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align:-.15em;margin-right:.25em"><path d="M21 12V7H5a2 2 0 0 1 0-4h14v4"></path><path d="M3 5v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h16v-5"></path><path d="M18 12a2 2 0 0 0 0 4h4v-4Z"></path></svg>AegisPay · <span style="color:var(--green)">Core on-chain testing complete</span></div>
      <h1>The last gate<br /><span class="gradient">before payment</span></h1>
      <p>
        Scams end in a transfer. AegisPay is a <b>risk-gating layer</b> that evaluates the
        conversation context before the user confirms a payment — built into AegisTalk.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="problem">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">// ARCHITECTURE</div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Non-custodial by design — AegisRD never holds customer funds</h2>
      <div class="ai-layers" style="max-width:880px">
        <div class="ai-layer reveal">
          <div class="layer-badge l1"><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align:-.15em;margin-right:.25em"><circle cx="7.5" cy="15.5" r="5.5"></circle><path d="m21 2-9.6 9.6"></path><path d="m15.5 7.5 3 3L22 7l-3-3"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="layer-info">
            <h4>Non-custodial smart-contract wallets</h4>
            <p>Users see a simple in-app stable balance (1 unit = 1 USDC). Funds live in the user's own ERC-4337 smart-contract wallet holding on-chain USDC. Signing keys are derived from the user's AegisID identity — AegisRD has no ability, at any time, to move customer funds.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-layer reveal">
          <div class="layer-badge l2"><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align:-.15em;margin-right:.25em"><line x1="3" y1="22" x2="21" y2="22"></line><line x1="6" y1="18" x2="6" y2="11"></line><line x1="10" y1="18" x2="10" y2="11"></line><line x1="14" y1="18" x2="14" y2="11"></line><line x1="18" y1="18" x2="18" y2="11"></line><polygon points="12 2 20 7 4 7"></polygon></svg></div>
          <div class="layer-info">
            <h4>Fiat on/off-ramp via licensed ramp partners</h4>
            <p>Fiat deposits and withdrawals are executed by regulated on/off-ramp service providers directly with the end user — including their KYC process. AegisRD does not provide exchange, custody, or issuance services.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-layer reveal">
          <div class="layer-badge l3"><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align:-.15em;margin-right:.25em"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"></path></svg></div>
          <div class="layer-info">
            <h4>AegisRD provides one thing: risk assessment</h4>
            <p>We see the <i>risk of a transaction</i>, never the <i>identity of the fiat customer</i>. Risk and identity are separated by design — a privacy guarantee and a compliance boundary.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ecosystem">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">// RISK GATING</div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Others see transactions. We understand the conversation.</h2>
      <div class="eco-grid">
        <div class="eco-card talk reveal">
          <div class="eco-step">Unique</div>
          <h3>Conversation-context gating</h3>
          <p>Transfers happen inside chats. AegisPay reuses AegisTalk's three-layer AI (L1/L2/L3) to score the scam risk of the surrounding conversation — high-risk payments enter a cooling-off delay and can be cancelled with one tap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card pay reveal">
          <div class="eco-step">Anti-impersonation</div>
          <h3>Signed payment codes</h3>
          <p>Payment request codes carry cryptographic signatures — forged codes simply fail verification.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card vpn reveal">
          <div class="eco-step">Identity</div>
          <h3>AegisID payee verification</h3>
          <p>Payees are bound to AegisID biometric feature vectors — you pay the verified person, not a lookalike account.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card track reveal">
          <div class="eco-step">Fees</div>
          <h3>Flat risk-service fee</h3>
          <p>A tiered flat fee (0.05 / 0.10 / 0.30 / 1.00 USDC per transaction) charged to the payer only. No percentage cut.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cost">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">// STATUS & COMPLIANCE</div>
      <h2 class="section-title reveal">Current status</h2>
      <div class="moat-col reveal" style="max-width:880px">
        <ul>
          <li><span class="check">✓</span> AegisPay's core functionality has <b>completed on-chain testing</b> (testnet: activation, top-up, instant transfer, risk time-lock, cancel &amp; refund, guardian alerts, withdrawal). No transaction service is offered before official launch; it ships with AegisTalk.</li>
          <li><span class="check">✓</span> KYC for fiat transactions is performed directly with users by regulated ramp providers.</li>
          <li><span class="check">✓</span> AegisRD provides risk-assessment technology only — no exchange, custody, or issuance services.</li>
          <li><span class="check">✓</span> On-chain asset: USDC, held in user-controlled ERC-4337 smart-contract wallets.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
